==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Methylal
<hw>Meth"yl*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Methyl</ets>ene + <ets>al</ets>cohol.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A light, volatile liquid,
<chform>H2C(OCH3)2</chform>, regarded as a complex ether, and having a
pleasant ethereal odor. It is obtained by the partial oxidation of
methyl alcohol. Called also <altname>formal</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Methylamine</ent>⟦br⟧
